<p>I made a custom listview, following is the code:</p>  <pre><code>ListView&lt;Sector&gt; sectorList = new ListView(); sectorList.setStyle("-fx-font-size: 21px;"); sectorList.setItems(data2); sectorList.setCellFactory(new Callback&lt;ListView&lt;Sector&gt;, ListCell&lt;Sector&gt;&gt;() {     @Override     public ListCell&lt;Sector&gt; call(ListView&lt;Sector&gt; param) {         return new XCell();     } }); </code></pre>  <p>.</p>  <pre><code>class XCell extends ListCell&lt;Sector&gt;{     @Override     protected void updateItem(Sector sector, boolean empty){         super.updateItem(sector, empty);         if(!empty){             CheckBox checkbox = new CheckBox(sector.getName());             checkbox.setStyle("-fx-font-weight: bold;");             checkbox.setSelected(true);              Label label = new Label("          "+sector.getDescription());             label.setStyle("-fx-font-style: italic;");              VBox root = new VBox(5);             root.setPadding(new Insets(8));             root.getChildren().addAll(checkbox,label);              setGraphic(root);         }else{             setGraphic(null);         }     } } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/DxiYU.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/DxiYU.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Is there a way to loop through the listview's items and check if the checkbox is selected or not? How?</p>